     <h2>The Pipeline Problem</h2>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="m-two-five">
      <p>9% of college graduates are majoring in computer science or engineering, only 17% of these graduates are female. According to the National Center for Education Statistics, women tend to major in health professions, social services, education, and psychology while men tend to major in computer sciences, physical sciences, fitness studies, and agriculture.</p>
      <p>This is called The Pipeline Problem &mdash; this means that because there aren't many women studying engineering, there are just not women available to fill these positions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
