  <div id="quitting" class="m-two-five">
    <h2>Why don't women stay?</h2>
    <p><span class="percent">56%</span> of women will quit engineering jobs within the first year of starting their career.</p>
    <p>
      Start ups have many qualities that allow for sexist problems to go without mention. Founders and employees are generally friends, which causes a blurry line between work and social life. Most small tech companies don’t have HR departments where employees feeling attacked or alone can turn to.
    </p>
    <p>
      It can be hard for women to voice their opinions and concerns to a company that is so heavily male dominated.
    </p> 
